premise_source_doc_sentence: In computing , an emulator is hardware or software that enables one computer system  (  called the host  )  to behave like another computer system  (  called the guest  )  .
Computer software , or simply software , is a part of a computer system that consists of data or computer instructions , in contrast to the physical hardware from which the system is built .

Power Plant HIL Simulator by Marine Cybernetics in Norway performs independent testing and verification of computer system software to detect and eliminate errors and weaknesses in power generators on ships , using Hardware-In-the-Loop  (  HIL  )  testing technology .
